setDescrip("Explores theoretical and methodological approaches to the cross-cultural study of 'race,' with an emphasis on historical and ethnographic analysis. Main approaches considered include Foucauldian, Gramscian, diaspora theory, and the everyday poetics and politics of race. (Formerly course 246).")
