setTitle("Archaeology Graduate Core Course: History of Archaeological Theory")
setTerms("F")
setDescrip("Historical overview of archaeology, concentrating on archaeological practice in the English-speaking world from the late 19th through the 21st Centuries. Emphasis is on development of archaeological theory in its social context; its relation to evolutionary and anthropological theory; and themes ongoing over time. Students cannot receive credit for this course and course 270.")
