setTerms("W")
setDescrip("Functions of several variables. Continuity and partial derivatives. The chain rule, gradient and directional derivative. Maxima and minima, including Lagrange multipliers. The double and triple integral and change of variables. Surface area and volumes. Applications from biology, chemistry, earth sciences, engineering, and physics. Students cannot receive credit for this course and course 23A.")
setPrereqs("course 11B or 19B or 20B or Applied Mathematics and Statistics 15B or AP calculus BC exam score of 4 or 5")
setGe("MF")
setInstruct("The Staff")
setCourse("23A")
setTitle("Vector Calculus")
setTerms("F,W,S")
setDescrip("Vectors in n-dimensional Euclidean space. The inner and cross products. The derivative of functions from n-dimensional to m-dimensional Euclidean space is studied as a linear transformation having matrix representation. Paths in 3-dimensions, arc length, vector differential calculus, Taylor's theorem in several variables, extrema of real-valued functions, constrained extrema and Lagrange multipliers, the implicit function theorem, some applications. Students cannot receive credit for this course and course 22. (Formerly Multivariable Calculus).")
setPrereqs("course 19B or 20B or AP calculus BC exam score of 4 or 5")
setGe("MF")
setInstruct("The Staff")
setCourse("23B")
setTitle("Vector Calculus")
setTerms("F,W,S")
setDescrip("Double integral, changing the order of integration. Triple integrals, maps of the plane, change of variables theorem, improper double integrals. Path integrals, line integrals, parametrized surfaces, area of a surface, surface integrals. Green's theorem, Stokes' theorem, conservative fields, Gauss' theorem. Applications to physics and differential equations, differential forms. (Formerly Multivariable Calculus).")
setPrereqs("course 23A")
setGe("MF")
setInstruct("The Staff")
